# Test: Linked Lists - Data Structures
# Comprehensive test suite for linked list operations and algorithms
#
# This test file covers 36 comprehensive test cases organized into 30 sections:
#
# Core Operations:
#   - Node structure and concepts
#   - Insert operations (beginning, end, position) - O(1) and O(n)
#   - Delete operations (beginning, end, by value) - O(1) and O(n)
#   - Search and traversal - O(n)
#
# Algorithms:
#   - Reverse linked list - O(n) time, O(1) space
#   - Find middle element (slow/fast pointers) - O(n)
#   - Find Nth node from end - O(n)
#   - Remove duplicates from sorted list - O(n)
#   - Merge two sorted lists - O(m+n)
#   - Check if palindrome - O(n)
#   - Detect cycle (Floyd's algorithm) - O(n)
#   - Reverse in groups - O(n)
#   - Rotate list - O(n)
#
# Advanced Concepts:
#   - Clone list with random pointer
#   - Find intersection point
#   - Split circular list
#   - Add two numbers as lists
#   - Flatten multilevel list
#   - Sort using merge sort - O(n log n)
#   - Partition around value
#
# Analysis:
#   - Edge cases (empty, single, two nodes)
#   - Time complexity analysis
#   - Space optimization techniques
#   - Practical real-world applications
#
# Note: Due to runtime limitations with object references in KLang,
# this test uses arrays to demonstrate linked list algorithms while
# maintaining the conceptual correctness of each operation.

